There are men who are fathers because they are your blood and there are men who are fathers because they choose to love you. Happy heavenly birthday to my bonus dad, the one and only Jimmie Lee Solomon. He changed Major League Baseball as the first black Executive Vice President of the sport, created a ladder to build opportunities for executives, players, coaches, and referees of color that lives beyond him… and he changed little 13 year old Grace Gibson’s life, when he walked into it and he chose to love me and pour into me for the rest of his days after my own father had passed a year before so no longer could. The hole left in the world without Jimmie Lee’s boisterous, generous, loving (and at times very loud lol) presence is profound…. But the impact he made will always be bigger because he was here and lives on through his legacy and those who love him. I miss him. Two and half years without him, without knowing I can call him whenever I need him, at any hour with any question, cry, or good news… well it feels like a lifetime. Love to all who are still mourning under your smiles and successes, because sometimes those moments of joy and triumph are the times we miss our angels most, those are the people we long to share it all with… well they are still with you, like the wind at your back guiding you to where you need to go. Thank you for guiding me Jimmie Lee, I love you forever. Happy birthday King.
Otw.

I’M MAKING MY FRENCH QUARTER FEST DEBUT! Saturday April 15th 3:30-4:40 pm on The Jack Daniels Stage (On the River Walk in-front of the aquarium) I’m SO excited to perform one of my favorite fests in my home city, I’ve always loved #FQF it’s so special and beautifully curated. Thanks for inviting me to join y’all this year @fqfest we have a fresh show in-store for you 🤗🫶🏾🤘🏾see you all on the Mississippi New Orleans! Cheers @jackdaniels_us 🍻 and special thanks to @jmoneyred for making it happen! 

#frenchquarter #frenchquarterfest #neworleans #jazzfestival

What a difference a year makes! Just a year ago I asked to be a guest of @justwynton to sing this song during his set at French Quarter Fest and now this year I’ve been invited to make my @fqfest debut with my own set on the same exact stage… cheers to progress🥂NEW ORLEANS See you Saturday April 15th at 3:30 pm on the Jack Daniels stage in front of The Aquarium. Let’s Geaux 🤘🏾Free festival so pull up 

PS: thank you @justwynton & @JT for your graciousness. I won’t forget it.

UPDATE: Our set has now been moved to 5 pm due to the rain. As of now we will reopen @fqfest with our set and attendees will be welcomed back to the stages (unless there is another downpour) hope to see ya at the Jack Daniel’s stage in front of the aquarium. Wish there was something I could do but God be funny like that lol 🤷🏾‍♀️ we will do our best to still play for y’all today, circumstances are sometimes out of our control🤘🏾

My debut at French Quarter Festival was so much fun🤍 I’m filled with gratitude from the love we received last weekend, the sleets of rain delayed but did not stop the show, the audience came back with pure energy, to see hundreds of smiling faces filled my heart as I sang on the coast of the Mississippi where my people landed in this country centuries ago and I’ll never forget it. This festival cemented my love for New Orleans music all those years ago when I moved to this city as a 3rd generation Louisianan musician… I’m grateful to have been invited to be a part of it this year. Thank you so much @fqfest and to my band @tissro @facemikebass @k._renaud @leshundaflake @jmoneyred And @jackdaniels_us 💜🫶🏾💜

A special thank you to the photographic legend @steverapportphotography for capturing such amazing shots, it’s an honor. Love you all, more to come 🫶🏾

Taking time to “water the good seeds.” 🌱🌿 and wear the last turtlenecks of the season😉

My bestie @jiezhen always tells me to water the fruitful seeds and people in your life… even when times are hard or you get fretful… look for the goodness and invest in it, smile as you plant… I got a lil under-the-weather after the amazing bustle of Jazz Fest, but it was good to slow down the past week and take some time to mediate on the the abundance of my life. I’m so grateful and will reflect that through my actions. Time to water and grow.

Only give me the mic if you ain’t scared.

Meeting Tina Turner as a baby is one of my first memories… For years I heard about her constantly as my father directed her biopic “What’s Love Got To Do With It” he was almost obsessed with getting it right… in a way I felt like she was a part of my family and like my life’s calling was baptized by her presence… like the path I’m on now is due to her, I have a lot of feelings about her & this that will take time to unpack, but mostly gratitude that she lived. Long live the queen of Rock’n’roll Tina Turner. Thank you for trusting my father Brian Gibson with your life story and forever changing mine. (I’ll probs post this caption again cause its that true to me)

TODAY IS MY BIRTHDAY!!! (And just the beginning of my birthday season 💃🏾) And I’m so deeply grateful… a few years ago I decided to reframe how I approached my birthdays and celebrate my years in color as opposed to number, a new theory I’m developing & I’ll tell you more about it later… but last year was my chartreuse year, the year before was indigo, and this is my marigold year… to be filled with orange hues of happiness, abundance, joy, prosperity and sunshine celebration. This past year has taught me too much to even attempt to list in one sitting so I’ll be sharing continuously, but for now I want to thank you all for supporting me through the years and promise the best are yet to come!!

Napa had my heart smiling💚 Woke up to picturesque vineyard views thanks to my new fave happy place @senzahotelnapa to start my birthday season🥰 

PS: guess who my travel buddy was? And why Napa was the destination of choice (other than for obvious reasons)😉swipe for cluesssss lol

New Orleans! This Sunday October 8th from 4:30-5:30 pm at The Chloe I’m doing an unplugged performance & talk highlighting my original songs and discussing my approach to creating music as the inaugural songwriter kicking of their new songwriting series and in celebration of The Chloe’s 3rd anniversary celebration. It’ll be free, stripped down, conversational, and causal (very different from my usual performances lol) featuring the wonderful @solomonthefox (who I’ve been making some new music with!) and great for ppl who are interested in the songwriting process and/or musicians. I’ll be doing a Q & A at the end! Come out and spend the afternoon with us in the porch of the beautiful @thechloenola (address: 4125 Saint Charles Ave, New Orleans)
